New Records: Victor Wembanyama had a career-high 50 points, making him the fourth-youngest player to achieve this feat, trailing only Brandon Jennings, LeBron James, and Devin Booker.
Wembanyama's previous high was 49 points in a previous game.
This is the eighth time in franchise history a player has scored 50 points.
Key Match Events: Wembanyama made an 18-foot jumper for his 49th and 50th points with 8:49 remaining, giving the Spurs a 115-98 lead.
Post-Match Reflections: Wembanyama's performance was a key factor in the Spurs' victory.
Jordan Poole had 42 points for the Wizards, but the Spurs managed to overcome this.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Wembanyama has made at least six 3-pointers for three straight games.
Wembanyama is the first player in league history with 20 3-pointers and 25 blocks over a six-game span.
Others: The Spurs will host the Los Angeles Lakers on Friday night.
The Wizards will face the Atlanta Hawks on Friday night.
